genresAdvancedInfo.name: greenlandic pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Greenlandic pop is a genre of popular music that originates from Greenland. It often features traditional Inuit music elements and lyrics that touch on themes of nature, culture, and identity. The genre has gained popularity in recent years, particularly among younger generations in Greenland and has helped to showcase the unique cultural heritage of the region to the rest of the world.
